      <t>This document defines the CCDR framework for traffic engineering within native IP network, using Dual/Multi-BGP session strategy and PCE-based central control architecture. The proposed central mode control framework conforms to the concept that defined in [RFC8283]. The scenario and simulation results of CCDR traffic engineering is described in draft [I-D.ietf-teas-native-ip-scenarios].</t>
